# Project Overview

This project, named Bridge23, is a superior team and community management platform built using Next.js and TypeScript. It provides automated planning and task execution capabilities for teams and communities.

# Key URLs
- Website: https://bridge23.app/
- Beta App: https://beta.bridge23.app/

# Project Structure
- **app/**: Next.js app directory for routing and pages
- **components/**: Reusable UI components
- **public/**: Static assets and images
- **types/**: TypeScript type definitions
- **styles/**: Global styles and CSS

# Development Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow the coding standards defined in ESLint configuration
- Ensure all components are responsive and accessible
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow the established design system and color palette

# Important Scripts
- `npm run dev`: Starts the development server
- `npm run build`: Builds the application for production
- `npm run start`: Runs the production server

# Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all new components and functions
- Follow React best practices and hooks guidelines
- Maintain consistent component structure
- Write clear, self-documenting code
- Handle errors gracefully and provide user feedback

# Component Guidelines
- Create reusable components in the components/ directory
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces
- Implement responsive design using Tailwind CSS
- Follow accessibility best practices
- Add proper documentation and props typing

